  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "This is in line with the qualitative analysis of Sect. 3.1, which showed that the signal is consistent with recent, upward-revised, SMBH-galaxy relations.",
    "There is also a slight preference for a high normalization of the pair fraction f 0 with a positive z dependence, β f > 1.",
    "Despite the low γ value favoured by the data, indicative of a flatter spectrum compared to the canonical value predicted by circular GW-driven binaries, SMBHB dynamics is largely unconstrained, perhaps with a marginal preference for eccentric binaries evolving in dense environments (e 0 and ζ 0 posteriors slightly rising towards the right bound of the prior).",
    "Altogether, these results point towards efficient orbital decay of SMBHBs in the aftermath of galaxy mergers, providing direct evidence that the 'final parsec problem' is solved in nature and that compact sub-parsec SMBHBs must be common in the centre of massive galaxies.",
    "We now explore the implication of this signal for the joint modelling of the galaxy and SMBH formation and evolution by taking a close look at two state-of-the-art SAMs: the model constructed by Barausse and collaborators (Barausse 2012; Sesana et al. 2014; Antonini et al. 2015; Klein et al. 2016; Bonetti et al. 2018; Barausse et al. 2020) and L-Galaxies (Henriques et al. 2015; Izquierdo-Villalba et al. 2022)."
  ],
